{
  "texts": [
    "It is well documented that molecules with many polar groups lack convergence in wavefunction optimization 61.",
    "The same applies when incorrect charges or protonation states are used.",
    "Implicit solvation substantially ameliorates the issue and masks problems.",
    "In fact, after determining the first guess for total molecular charges, single-point-energy calculations on unrefined ligands using implicit water required roughly 6 h of computation time.",
    "Turning off implicit solvation increased the calculation time to almost three weeks on the same machine."
  ]
}